classes.label: EsqlQuery
description:
Represents a parsed or programmatically created ES|QL query. Keeps track of
the AST, source code, and optionally lexer tokens.

classes.label: Walker
description:
Iterates over all nodes in the AST and calls the appropriate visitor
functions.

children.label: walk
description: Walks the AST and calls the appropriate visitor functions.

children.label: find
description: Finds and returns the first node that matches the search criteria.

children.label: tree
description: AST node to start the search from.

children.label: predicate
description: A function that returns true if the node matches the search criteria.

returnComment: The first node that matches the search criteria.

children.label: findAll
description: Finds and returns all nodes that match the search criteria.

children.label: tree
description: AST node to start the search from.

children.label: predicate

children.label: match
description:
Matches a single node against a template object. Returns the first node
that matches the template. The *template* object is a sparse representation
of the node structure, where each property corresponds to a node type or
property to match against.

- An array matches if the node key is in the array.
- A RegExp matches if the node key matches the RegExp.
- Any other value matches if the node key is triple-equal to the value.

For example, match the first `literal`:

```typescript
const literal = Walker.match(ast, { type: 'literal' });
```

Find the first `literal` with a specific value:

```typescript
const number42 = Walker.match(ast, { type: 'literal', value: 42 });
```

Find the first literal of type `integer` or `decimal`:

```typescript
const number = Walker.match(ast, {
  type: 'literal',
  literalType: [ 'integer', 'decimal' ],
});
```

Finally, you can also match any field by regular expression. Find
the first `source` AST node, which has "log" in its name:

```typescript
const logSource = Walker.match(ast, { type: 'source', name: /.+log.+/ });
```

children.label: template

children.label: parent
description:
Returns the parent node of the given child node.

For example, if the child node is a source node, this method will return
the `FROM` command that contains the source:

```typescript
const { ast } = EsqlQuery.fromSrc('FROM index');
const child = Walker.match(ast, { type: 'source' });
const parent = Walker.parent(ast, child); // FROM
const grandParent = Walker.parent(ast, parent); // query expression
```

children.label: child
description: The child node for which to find the parent.

returnComment: The parent node of the child, if found.

children.label: parents
description:
Returns an array of parent nodes for the given child node.
This method traverses the AST upwards from the child node
and collects all parent nodes until it reaches the root. The
most immediate parent is the first element in the array,
and the root node is the last element.

children.label: tree
description: AST node to search in.

children.label: child
description: The child node for which to find the parents.

returnComment: An array of parent nodes for the child, if found.

children.label: visitComments
description:
Visits all comment nodes in the AST. Comments are part of the *hidden*
channel and normally not part of the AST. To parse the comments, you
need to run the parser with `withFormatting` option set to `true`.

children.label: tree
description: AST node to search in.

children.label: callback
description:
Callback function that is called for each comment node.
The callback receives the comment node, the node it is attached to,
and the attachment type (top, left, right, rightSingleLine, bottom).

functions.label: isBinaryExpression
description:
Returns true if the given node is a binary expression, i.e. an operator
surrounded by two operands:

```
1 + 1
column LIKE "foo"
foo = "bar"
```

children.label: node
description: Any ES|QL AST node.

functions.label: lastItem
description: Returns the last normalized "single item" from the "item" list.

children.label: items
description: Returns the last "single item" from the "item" list.

functions.label: singleItems
description: Normalizes AST "item" list to only contain *single* items.

children.label: items
description: A list of single or nested items.

children.label: multiline
description:
Whether to break the query into multiple lines on each pipe. Defaults to
`false`.

children.label: pipeTab
description:
Tabbing string inserted before a pipe, when `multiline` is `true`. Defaults
to two spaces.

children.label: lowercase
description: The default lowercase setting to use for all options. Defaults to `false`.

children.label: lowercaseCommands
description: Whether to lowercase command names. Defaults to `false`.

children.label: lowercaseOptions
description: Whether to lowercase command options. Defaults to `false`.

children.label: lowercaseFunctions
description: Whether to lowercase function names. Defaults to `false`.

children.label: lowercaseKeywords
description: Whether to lowercase keywords. Defaults to `false`.

children.label: args
description:
A ES|QL column name can be composed of multiple parts,
e.g: part1.part2.`part``3`.?param. Where parts can be quoted, or not
quoted, or even be a parameter.

The args list contains the parts of the column name.

children.label: parts
description:
An identifier can be composed of multiple parts, e.g: part1.part2.`part``3`.
This property contains the parsed unquoted parts of the identifier.
For example: `['part1', 'part2', 'part`3']`.

children.label: commandType
description:
The subtype of the command. For example, the `JOIN` command can be: (1)
LOOKUP JOIN, (2) LEFT JOIN, (3) RIGHT JOIN.

children.label: subtype
description: Default is 'variadic-call'.

children.label: operator
description: A node representing the function or operator being called.

children.label: prefix
description:
Represents the prefix part of the source identifier. Empty string if not
present. Used in index pattern as the cluster identifier or as "mode" in
enrich policy.

```
FROM [<prefix>:]<index>
```

children.label: index
description:
Represents the index part of the source identifier. Unescaped and unquoted.

```
FROM [<cluster>:]<index>
```

children.label: selector
description:
Represents the selector (component) part of the source identifier.

```
FROM <index>[::<selector>]
```

children.label: withFormatting
description:
Whether to collect and attach to AST nodes user's custom formatting:
comments and whitespace.

children.label: root
description: The root *QueryExpression* node of the parsed tree.

children.label: ast
description: List of parsed commands.

children.label: tokens
description: List of ANTLR tokens generated by the lexer.

children.label: errors
description: List of parsing errors.

children.label: visitSingleAstItem
description: Called on every expression node.

children.label: visitAny
description: Called for any node type that does not have a specific visitor.

children.label: node
description: Any valid AST node.

children.label: order
description:
Order in which to traverse child nodes. If set to 'forward', child nodes
are traversed in the order they appear in the AST. If set to 'backward',
child nodes are traversed in reverse order.

children.label: indent
description:
Initial indentation string inserted before the whole query. Defaults to an
empty string.

children.label: tab
description: Tabbing string inserted before new level of nesting. Defaults to two spaces.

children.label: pipeTab
description: Tabbing string inserted before a pipe, when `multiline` is `true`.

children.label: commandTab
description:
Tabbing string inserted before command arguments, when they are broken into
multiple lines. Defaults to four spaces.

children.label: multiline
description:
Whether to force multiline formatting. Defaults to `false`. If set to
`false`, it will try to fit the query into a single line.

children.label: wrap
description:
Expected width of the output. Defaults to 80 characters. Text will be
wrapped to fit this width.

misc.label: AstNodeParserFields
description:
Node fields which are available only when the node is minted by the parser.
When creating nodes manually, these fields are not available.

misc.label: AstNodeTemplate
description:
The node *template* transforms ES|QL AST nodes into a permissive shape, with
the aim to:

- Remove the `type` property, as the builder will set it.
- Make properties like `text`, `location`, and `incomplete` optional, as they
  are a available only when the AST node is minted by the parser.
- Make all other properties optional, for easy node creation.

misc.label: BasicPrettyPrinterMultilineOptions
signature: { lowercase?: boolean | undefined; pipeTab?: string | undefined; lowercaseCommands?: boolean | undefined; lowercaseOptions?: boolean | undefined; lowercaseFunctions?: boolean | undefined; lowercaseKeywords?: boolean | undefined; }

misc.label: ESQLAstItem
description:
An array of AST nodes represents different things in different contexts.
For example, in command top level arguments it is treated as an "assignment expression".

objects.label: LeafPrinter
description:
Printer for leaf AST nodes. The printing output of these nodes should
typically not depend on word wrapping settings, should always return an
atomic short string.
